label.value: peripheral B cell selection

value.value: Any B cell selection process that occurs in the periphery.

label.value: B cell affinity maturation

value.value: The process in which B cells produce antibodies with increased antigen affinity. This is accomplished by somatic hypermutation and selection for B cells which produce higher affinity antibodies to antigen.

label.value: histamine production involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The synthesis or release of histamine following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label.value: serotonin production involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The synthesis or release of serotonin following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label.value: leukocyte activation involved in immune response

value.value: A change in morphology and behavior of a leukocyte resulting from exposure to a specific antigen, mitogen, cytokine, cellular ligand, or soluble factor, leading to the initiation or perpetuation of an immune response.

label.value: cytokine production involved in immune response

value.value: The appearance of a cytokine due to biosynthesis or secretion following a cellular stimulus contributing to an immune response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

definition.value: Note that this term is in the subset of terms that should not be used for direct gene product annotation. Instead, select one of the 'regulation' children terms.

label.value: immune system process

value.value: Any process involved in the development or functioning of the immune system, an organismal system for calibrated responses to potential internal or invasive threats.

definition.value: Note that this term is a direct child of 'biological_process ; GO:0008150' because some immune system processes are types of cellular process (GO:0009987), whereas others are types of multicellular organism process (GO:0032501).

label.value: immunoglobulin production

value.value: The appearance of immunoglobulin due to biosynthesis or secretion following a cellular stimulus, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

definition.value: Note that this term is in the subset of terms that should not be used for direct gene product annotation. Instead, select one of the 'regulation' children terms.

label.value: immunoglobulin production involved in immunoglobulin-mediated immune response

value.value: The appearance of immunoglobulin due to biosynthesis or secretion following a cellular stimulus during an immune response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

definition.value: Note that this term is in the subset of terms that should not be used for direct gene product annotation. Instead, select one of the 'regulation' children terms.

label.value: hepatic immune response

value.value: An immune response taking place in the liver.

label.value: production of molecular mediator of immune response

value.value: The synthesis or release of any molecular mediator of the immune response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

definition.value: Note that this term is in the subset of terms that should not be used for direct gene product annotation. Instead, select one of the 'regulation' children terms.

label.value: histamine secretion involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The regulated release of histamine by a cell as part of an inflammatory response.

label.value: serotonin secretion involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The regulated release of serotonin by a cell as part of an inflammatory response.

label.value: leukocyte mediated immunity

value.value: Any process involved in the carrying out of an immune response by a leukocyte.

label.value: myeloid leukocyte mediated immunity

value.value: Any process involved in the carrying out of an immune response by a myeloid leukocyte.

label.value: neutrophil mediated immunity

value.value: Any process involved in the carrying out of an immune response by a neutrophil.

label.value: lymphocyte mediated immunity

value.value: Any process involved in the carrying out of an immune response by a lymphocyte.

label.value: T cell mediated immunity

value.value: Any process involved in the carrying out of an immune response by a T cell.

label.value: adaptive immune response based on somatic recombination of immune receptors built from immunoglobulin superfamily domains

value.value: An immune response mediated by lymphocytes expressing specific receptors for antigen produced through a somatic diversification process that includes somatic recombination of germline gene segments encoding immunoglobulin superfamily domains. Recombined receptors for antigen encoded by immunoglobulin superfamily domains include T cell receptors and immunoglobulins (antibodies) produced by B cells. The first encounter with antigen elicits a primary immune response that is slow and not of great magnitude. T and B cells selected by antigen become activated and undergo clonal expansion. A fraction of antigen-reactive T and B cells become memory cells, whereas others differentiate into effector cells. The memory cells generated during the primary response enable a much faster and stronger secondary immune response upon subsequent exposures to the same antigen (immunological memory). An example of this is the adaptive immune response found in Mus musculus.

label.value: tolerance induction dependent upon immune response

value.value: Tolerance induction dependent upon an immune response, typically a response by a mature T or B cell in the periphery resulting tolerance towards an antigen via induction of anergy, cellular deletion, or regulatory T cell activation.

label.value: peripheral tolerance induction

value.value: Tolerance induction in the peripheral lymphoid tissues: blood, lymph nodes, spleen, and mucosal-associated lymphoid tissues.

label.value: germinal center formation

value.value: The process in which germinal centers form. A germinal center is a specialized microenvironment formed when activated B cells enter lymphoid follicles. Germinal centers are the foci for B cell proliferation and somatic hypermutation.

label.value: antigen processing and presentation of peptide or polysaccharide antigen via MHC class II

value.value: The process in which an antigen-presenting cell expresses antigen (peptide or polysaccharide) on its cell surface in association with an MHC class II protein complex.

label.value: tolerance induction

value.value: A process that directly activates any of the steps required for tolerance, a physiologic state in which the immune system does not react destructively against the components of an organism that harbors it or against antigens that are introduced to it.

label.value: immune system development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an organismal system whose objective is to provide calibrated responses by an organism to a potential internal or invasive threat, over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A system is a regularly interacting or interdependent group of organs or tissues that work together to carry out a given biological process.

label.value: leukocyte differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized hemopoietic precursor cell acquires the specialized features of a leukocyte. A leukocyte is an achromatic cell of the myeloid or lymphoid lineages capable of ameboid movement, found in blood or other tissue.

label.value: leukocyte migration involved in immune response

value.value: The movement of a leukocyte within or between different tissues and organs of the body as part of an immune response.

label.value: leukocyte migration involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The movement of a leukocyte within or between different tissues and organs of the body contributing to an inflammatory response.

label.value: acute inflammatory response

value.value: Inflammation which comprises a rapid, short-lived, relatively uniform response to acute injury or antigenic challenge and is characterized by accumulations of fluid, plasma proteins, and granulocytic leukocytes. An acute inflammatory response occurs within a matter of minutes or hours, and either resolves within a few days or becomes a chronic inflammatory response.

label.value: production of molecular mediator involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The synthesis or release of any molecular mediator of the inflammatory response following an inflammatory stimulus, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label.value: cytokine production involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The synthesis or release of a cytokine following a inflammatory stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label.value: respiratory burst involved in inflammatory response

value.value: A phase of elevated metabolic activity, during which oxygen consumption increases following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response; this leads to the production, by an NADH dependent system, of hydrogen peroxide (H2O2), superoxide anions and hydroxyl radicals, resulting in an increase in their intracellular or extracellular levels.

label.value: arachidonic acid metabolite production involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The synthesis or release of products of arachidonic acid metabolism following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in their intracellular or extracellular levels.

label.value: prostaglandin production involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The synthesis or release of any prostaglandin following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label.value: chronic inflammatory response

value.value: Inflammation of prolonged duration (weeks or months) in which active inflammation, tissue destruction, and attempts at repair are proceeding simultaneously. Although it may follow acute inflammation, chronic inflammation frequently begins insidiously, as a low-grade, smoldering, often asymptomatic response.

label.value: monocyte chemotaxis

value.value: The movement of a monocyte in response to an external stimulus.

label.value: somatic diversification of immune receptors via germline recombination within a single locus

value.value: The process in which immune receptor genes are diversified through recombination of the germline genetic elements within a single genetic locus.

label.value: somatic diversification of immune receptors via somatic mutation

value.value: The process in which immune receptor genes are diversified through somatic mutation.

label.value: myeloid leukocyte differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized myeloid precursor cell acquires the specialized features of any cell of the myeloid leukocyte lineage.

label.value: thrombocyte differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized myeloid precursor cell acquires the specialized features of a thrombocyte, a nucleated cell found in all vertebrates but mammals involved in hemostasis.

definition.value: Note that platelets are the non-nucleated mammalian functional equivalent of the nucleated thrombocytes of non-mammalian vertebrates and are sometimes also referred to as thrombocytes. Platelet formation in mammals is covered by the biological_process term platelet formation ; GO:0030220.

label.value: regulation of antigen processing and presentation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of antigen processing and presentation.

label.value: negative regulation of antigen processing and presentation

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of antigen processing and presentation.

label.value: positive regulation of antigen processing and presentation

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of antigen processing and presentation.

label.value: regulation of antigen processing and presentation of peptide or polysaccharide antigen via MHC class II

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of antigen processing and presentation of antigen (peptide or polysaccharide) via MHC class II.

label.value: negative regulation of antigen processing and presentation of peptide or polysaccharide antigen via MHC class II

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of antigen processing and presentation of antigen (peptide or polysaccharide) via MHC class II.

label.value: positive regulation of antigen processing and presentation of peptide or polysaccharide antigen via MHC class II

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of antigen processing and presentation of antigen (peptide or polysaccharide) via MHC class II.

label.value: regulation of germinal center formation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of germinal center formation.

label.value: negative regulation of germinal center formation

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of germinal center formation.

label.value: positive regulation of germinal center formation

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of germinal center formation.

label.value: regulation of immunoglobulin production

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of immunoglobulin production.
